    {
      "created": "2026-05-18T11:22:49.166921+00:00",
      "modified": "2026-05-18T11:22:49.433616+00:00",
      "id": 20269810,
      "conceptrecid": "15780708",
      "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.20269810",
      "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.15780708",
      "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20269810",
      "metadata": {
        "title": "FRA: Dark Matter as \u03b4-Interference, Dark Energy as Fractal Growth",
        "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.20269810",
        "publication_date": "2026-05-18",
        "description": "<p>Known Discrepancies and Methodological Limitations</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This release provides a working operational prototype, but it also exposes several systematic limitations in the NGC 2403 test case.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1. Outer Rotation Curve Deviation</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The FRA-derived dark-matter component V_DM(FRA 1D) captures part of the inner rise, especially in the 2&ndash;6 kpc region, but declines too steeply at larger radii compared with the observationally inferred V_DM(obs). This indicates that the current 1D proxy, default channel weights, and smoothing scale do not yet fully reproduce the extended outer-halo contribution.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2. Geometric Approximation</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The present mass recovery uses a spherical approximation:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>M(&lt;r) = &int; 4&pi;r&sup2; &rho;(r) dr.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For flattened disk galaxies such as NGC 2403, this can introduce systematic bias in the recovered density and velocity profiles, especially at large radii. A future version should replace this step with an axisymmetric disk potential or a numerical Poisson solver adapted to disk geometry.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3. Kinematic Proxy for &delta;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In this v2.0.0 release, the FRA contrast field &delta; is derived from radial gradients of SPARC velocity components, such as V_gas, V_disk, and V_bul. These quantities already encode part of the gravitational structure that the model later attempts to reconstruct.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Therefore, this version should be treated as an operational reconstruction prototype, not yet as a fully independent prediction. A fully predictive v3.0+ version should derive &delta; from structural maps independent of rotation-curve kinematics, such as gas surface density &Sigma;_gas, stellar photometry, SFR maps, baryonic-potential gradients, and HI shear fields.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4. Calibration Scope</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The coupling coefficient &kappa; is currently calibrated at a single reference radius:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>R_target = 8.0 kpc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This is acceptable for a controlled single-galaxy prototype, but not sufficient for a universal claim. Statistical robustness requires testing &kappa; across a larger SPARC sample and checking whether it remains stable globally, or at least within well-defined galaxy classes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5. Current Status</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This release should be read as a phenomenological and computational prototype.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It demonstrates the operational chain:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&delta; &rarr; &sigma;_&delta; &rarr; &rho;_DM &rarr; M(r) &rarr; V_FRA(r),</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>but it does not yet claim to replace &Lambda;CDM or standard halo models.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Next steps include:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- replacing kinematic &delta;-proxies with density-based structural &delta;-fields;</p>\n<p>- implementing disk-aware or axisymmetric gravitational recovery;</p>\n<p>- testing the method across the full SPARC sample;</p>\n<p>- comparing RMSE, &chi;&sup2;, AIC, and BIC against NFW, MOND, and other standard models;</p>\n<p>- evaluating whether &kappa; is stable globally or only within specific morphological classes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This limitation record is included intentionally to make the prototype falsifiable, reproducible, and methodologically transparent.</p>",
        "access_right": "restricted",
        "creators": [
          {
            "name": "AdmailFRA",
            "affiliation": null
          }
        ],
